PROTOCOL ID (Required): A unique ID for the protocol.
PROTOCOL NAME: A short name for the protocol.
PROTOCOL DESCRIPTION: A general description of the protocol.
PUBLICATION DOI: The publication digital object identifier (doi) for the protocol.
PROTOCOLS.IO DOI: The protocols.io digital object identifier (doi) for the protocol.
DOCUMENT FILENAME: A filename of a PDF document containing the details of the protocol.
INSTRUMENT (Required): The full name of the instrument used.
INSTRUMENT ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession
INSTRUMENT ONTOLOGY LABEL: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field
LOCAL MACHINE NAME: Local name for the particular machine used for sequencing.
PAIRED END? (Required): Whether the sequenced molecule was sequenced from both ends.
SEQUENCING APPROACH (Required): The name of a sequencing approach being used.
SEQUENCING APPROACH ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession
SEQUENCING APPROACH ONTOLOGY LABEL: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field

PROTOCOL ID (Required): Protocol ID should have no spaces.
INSTRUMENT (Required): For example: Illumina HiSeq 2500; ONT MinION
INSTRUMENT ONTOLOGY LABEL: For example: Illumina HiSeq 2500; ONT MinION
PAIRED END? (Required): If 3' 10x v2 was used, enter no. For example: Should be one of: yes, or no.
SEQUENCING APPROACH (Required): For example: tag based single cell RNA sequencing; full length single cell RNA sequencing
SEQUENCING APPROACH ONTOLOGY LABEL: For example: tag based single cell RNA sequencing; full length single cell RNA sequencing
